WEBVTT

00:04.152 --> 00:07.349
We got a burn notice on you,
you're black listed.

00:07.384 --> 00:09.750
<i>When you're burned,
you've got nothing --</i>

00:09.785 --> 00:12.337
<i>No cash, no credit,
no job history.</i>

00:12.372 --> 00:14.732
<i>You're stuck in whatever city
they decide to dump you in.</i>

00:14.767 --> 00:16.446
Where am I?
Miami.

00:16.447 --> 00:19.004
<i>You do whatever work
comes your way.</i>

00:19.039 --> 00:22.594
<i>You rely on anyone
who's still talking to you.</i>

00:22.629 --> 00:25.660
<i>A trigger-happy ex-girlfriend...
Should we shoot them?</i>

00:25.695 --> 00:28.299
<i>...An old friend who used
to inform on you to the fbi...</i>

00:28.334 --> 00:30.493
You know spies --
a bunch of bitchy little girls.

00:30.528 --> 00:32.894
<i>...Family, too...
Hey, is that your mom again?</i>

00:32.929 --> 00:35.430
<i>...If you're desperate.
Someone needs your help,
michael.</i>

00:35.465 --> 00:37.884
<i>Bottom line --
as long as you're burned,</i>

00:37.919 --> 00:40.460
<i>You're not going anywhere.</i>

00:45.040 --> 00:46.913
<i>It's never fun to be the guy</i>

00:46.914 --> 00:49.065
<i>Who clears a location
for a meet.</i>

00:49.100 --> 00:50.936
<i>In the best case,
you waste your time</i>

00:50.937 --> 00:52.921
<i>Looking for dangers
that aren't there.</i>

00:52.956 --> 00:56.204
<i>In the worst case, of course,
you miss something.</i>

00:58.115 --> 01:01.028
Hey, your buddy went in
10 minutes ago, alone.

01:01.063 --> 01:02.877
Sam, you didn't
have to scout this for me.

01:02.878 --> 01:06.042
Come on, mikey,
I am not gonna let you
Meet a guy like gilroy
without backup.

01:06.077 --> 01:09.127
If he was planning on killing me,
I doubt he'd pick such a nice place.

01:09.162 --> 01:10.726
Do you know how hard it is
to get a reservation in there?

01:10.727 --> 01:12.669
Yeah, and I know
what they serve in there, too --

01:12.704 --> 01:13.935
Foie gras...

01:13.936 --> 01:15.836
"lap-in."

01:15.996 --> 01:17.551
<i>Lapin?</i>

01:17.552 --> 01:19.302
Yeah, whatever. It's still
french for "bunny rabbit."

01:19.303 --> 01:20.762
Look, I'm all for
bringing gilroy down,

01:20.763 --> 01:22.537
But isn't there a way
to wrap this guy up

01:22.538 --> 01:23.588
Without actually
working with him?

01:23.589 --> 01:25.117
I went to a lot of trouble
to convince him

01:25.118 --> 01:27.174
I'm as much of a psychopath
as he is.

01:27.209 --> 01:28.842
Might as well hear
what he has planned.

01:28.843 --> 01:31.008
Odds are he's not gonna ask you
to walk his dog for him.

01:31.043 --> 01:32.369
Well, I don't have
much choice.

01:32.370 --> 01:34.587
<i>Whatever he is planning,
the only way to stop it</i>

01:34.622 --> 01:36.722
Is to be right
in the middle of it.

01:36.757 --> 01:38.345
<i>Bon appÃ©tit.</i>

01:38.346 --> 01:41.273
That's french for
"watch your back, amigo."

01:41.308 --> 01:43.738
<i>Even routine meetings
can be risky</i>

01:43.773 --> 01:46.012
<i>If you're sitting down
with someone you don't trust.</i>

01:46.047 --> 01:48.365
<i>You have to be alert
to any subtle clue</i>

01:48.400 --> 01:50.321
<i>That tells you
what you're walking into.</i>

01:53.299 --> 01:55.704
<i>Are they armed?
Did they bring backup?</i>

01:58.335 --> 01:59.998
<i>Of course, there are also
not-so-subtle clues...</i>

01:59.999 --> 02:02.942
Glad you could make it.
I hope you don't mind.

02:02.977 --> 02:05.550
I took the liberty of ordering
an appetizer to start.

02:05.585 --> 02:08.967
<i>...Like a third place setting
at a lunch for two.</i>

02:09.002 --> 02:10.509
We expecting
someone else?

02:10.511 --> 02:12.390
I didn't tell you?
Claude should be here.

02:12.391 --> 02:13.039
Claude?

02:13.040 --> 02:15.434
Wonderful chap.
Excellent conversationalist.

02:15.469 --> 02:16.988
Has great fashion sense,

02:16.989 --> 02:18.945
And he's the best thief
in the western hemisphere.

02:18.980 --> 02:21.760
Useful skill in this phase
of our little project.

02:21.795 --> 02:23.276
I don't mind sharing a meal
with him,

02:23.277 --> 02:25.020
But, uh, I prefer
to work alone.

02:25.021 --> 02:27.314
Don't be so hasty, michael.
You'll like claude.

02:27.349 --> 02:29.701
His rÃ©sumÃ© is almost
as nasty as yours.

02:29.736 --> 02:32.149
Working with someone you don't
know is stupid and dangerous.

02:32.184 --> 02:34.020
Look who's full
of theories.

02:34.021 --> 02:36.225
Well, I'm afraid you'll have to
make an exception this time,

02:36.260 --> 02:38.151
Learn the value
of teamwork.

02:38.152 --> 02:40.167
No thanks.

02:41.631 --> 02:43.484
Claude, michael.

02:43.485 --> 02:45.002
Michael, claude.

02:45.003 --> 02:47.097
So, this is
your local boy?

02:48.001 --> 02:50.814
Actually, michael's not sure
he can stay for lunch.

02:50.849 --> 02:53.544
Decision time.

03:01.275 --> 03:03.195
Splendid.

03:03.230 --> 03:05.440
Let's get some wine, shall we?
To celebrate.

03:05.475 --> 03:08.531
Something old, french,
and...Expensive.

